transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Viagra, I can help you today.

Speaker 2: Yes, good morning.

Speaker 1: I need to cancel my prescription.

Speaker 2: I can take a look into that for you.

Speaker 1: What's your zip code and your last name?

Speaker 2: Zip code is 84009, Lucius, L-U-C-I-U-S.

Speaker 1: And what's your first name?

Speaker 2: Allen, A-L-L-E-N.

Speaker 1: Hi, Dr. Poliotzer, so I do want to mention

Speaker 2: how you're currently one of our VIP members

Speaker 1: for the Pfizer-Viagra AGV.

Speaker 2: The moment I cancel out the prescription,

Speaker 1: unfortunately, you wouldn't be able to access

Speaker 2: these pills anymore.

Speaker 1: I could always freeze it out for you.

Speaker 2: Okay, that's fine.

Speaker 1: If you like, instead, that way you can retain access

Speaker 2: to it for when you need it.

Speaker 1: No, I don't. I don't need it anymore.

Speaker 2: Got it. All right, I'll go ahead

Speaker 1: and just stop those orders for you.

Speaker 2: Just keep in mind, sir, moving forward,

Speaker 1: unfortunately, you wouldn't be able to access this anymore.

Speaker 2: That's fine. And then with that being said,

Speaker 1: do you have an operator number or...

Speaker 2: No, no number, just prescription's been fully deleted

Speaker 1: and you won't be able to access them

Speaker 2: even if you wanted to, but you're all set.

Speaker 1: All right, thank you so much.

Speaker 2: No problem. Have a good one.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
